<DOC><DOCNO> AP880721-0290 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-21-88 1435EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d f AM-Germany-Airbus     07-21 0109</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Germany-Airbus,0116</SECOND><HEAD>Lufthansa Orders Four Airbuses Worth $270 Million</HEAD><DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The West German airline Lufthansaon Thursday said it will purchase four additional Airbus jets for atotal of about $270 million.   Three of the planes are A300-310s and one is a larger A300-600.All of the planes can carry about 200 passengers.   The purchase of an additional four planes will bring thecarrier's fleet of Airbus planes to 28.   Delivery is scheduled to take place between November 1989 andFebruary 1990.   Airbus Industrie is a consortium comprising Aerospatiale ofFrance, British Aerospace PLC, Spain's Construccionnes AeronauticasSA and Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm GmbH of West Germany.</TEXT></DOC>